cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with identifying and annotating metaphor in corpora. It also involves the use of a neural network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions transfer learning, which is a common technique in the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of user annotations as training data also suggests a possible connection to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the specific application of the neural network to classify metaphorical violence on cable news may fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
